{
  "benchmark_id": "croniter",
  "description": "Cron next-fire computation modelled on the croniter library: cronMatches/nextFire/prevFire on a discretised minute/hour/day-of-week clock, with witness-minimality (and symmetric witness-maximality) specs anchored on the frozen field extractors minOf/hourOf/dowOf. Beyond the witness/extremal specs the suite carries hidden-invariant families that require a discovered strengthened induction hypothesis: forward and backward aggregate window-count laws (gap/step/k-th counts, multi-week density = k·per-week count), nextFire/prevFire adjacency and inverse laws on firing minutes, prevFire monotonicity, multi-week shift-equivariance, and a one-period-of-fires-spans-one-week iteration law. Scope: this models a parsed 3-field (minute / hour / day-of-week) scheduler over `Nat` absolute minutes — there is no cron-expression parser, no seconds / year / day-of-month / month fields, and no `day_or` / timezone handling.",
